GHG_leb

GHG and LEB

This is a preliminary analysis to look at Per Capita GHG emissions and Life Expectancy at birth. It uses data from the UC Berekely CoolClimate Map* (zip code level) and from the Healthy Places Index website (census tract level).

*Christopher M. Jones and Daniel M. Kammen, Spatial Distribution of U.S. Household Carbon Footprints Reveals Suburbanization Undermines Greenhouse Gas Benefits of Urban Population Density. Environ. Sci. Technol., 2013, dx.doi.org/10.1021/es4034364

health <- read.csv("~/GHG_leb/HPIhealthOutcomes.csv", header=T) %>% 
   mutate(ct10= as.character(paste0("0",geoid)))
GHG <- read.csv("~/GHG_leb/CoolClimateZips.csv", header=T, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

Check out GHG data

We have data for the whole country but can only compare to LEB within CA.

GHG %>% filter(State == "CA") %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_point(aes(x=popden, y=Vehicle.miles.traveled)) +
    geom_smooth(aes(x=popden, y=Vehicle.miles.traveled), method = "loess") +
  theme_fivethirtyeight() + ggtitle("VMT vs PopDensity")

GHG %>% filter(State == "CA") %>% 
  rename(transport = Transport..tCO2e.yr.,
         housing = Housing..tCO2e.yr.,
         food = Food..tCO2e.yr.,
         goods =  Goods..tCO2e.yr.,
         services = Services..tCO2e.yr., 
         total = Total..tCO2e.yr.) %>%
  gather(transport, housing, food, goods, services, total, key = "Category",value = "emissions") %>%
  filter(Category != "total") %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_point(aes(x=popden, y=emissions, color=Category), alpha=0.1) +
    geom_smooth(aes(x=popden, y=emissions, color=Category, group= Category), method = "glm") +
  guides(alpha = FALSE) +
  theme_fivethirtyeight() + 
  scale_colour_wsj() + ggtitle("PerCapita Carbon Emissions vs. PopDensity")

Get Spatial

Link the tables to spatial information.

tracts <- st_read("~/CHVI_copy/data/shapefiles/census_tracts2010.shp") %>% 
  st_transform(crs = 4326) %>%
  left_join(health)
## Reading layer `census_tracts2010' from data source `C:\Users\jvargo\Documents\CHVI_copy\data\shapefiles\census_tracts2010.shp' using driver `ESRI Shapefile'
## Simple feature collection with 8048 features and 13 fields
## geometry type:  MULTIPOLYGON
## dimension:      XY
## bbox:           xmin: -373976.1 ymin: -604512.6 xmax: 539719.6 ymax: 450022.5
## epsg (SRID):    NA
## proj4string:    +proj=aea +lat_1=34 +lat_2=40.5 +lat_0=0 +lon_0=-120 +x_0=0 +y_0=-4000000 +datum=NAD83 +units=m +no_defs
## Joining, by = "ct10"
GHGpt <- st_as_sf(GHG, coords = c("Longitude", "Latitude"), crs = 4326)

intersect <- st_intersection(x = tracts, y =GHGpt)
## although coordinates are longitude/latitude, st_intersection assumes that they are planar
intersect %>% 
  rename(transport = Transport..tCO2e.yr.,
         housing = Housing..tCO2e.yr.,
         food = Food..tCO2e.yr.,
         goods =  Goods..tCO2e.yr.,
         services = Services..tCO2e.yr., 
         total = Total..tCO2e.yr.)  %>%
  gather(transport, housing, food, goods, services, total, key = "Category",value = "emissions") %>%
  filter(Category != "total") %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_point(aes(y=leb, x=emissions, color=Category), alpha=I(0.05)) +
    geom_smooth(aes(y=leb, x=emissions, color=Category, group= Category), method = "glm") + 
  guides(alpha = FALSE) +
  theme_fivethirtyeight() + 
  scale_colour_wsj() + ggtitle("PerCap CO2equiv vs. Life Expectancy") + facet_wrap(~ Category)

intersect %>% 
  rename(transport = Transport..tCO2e.yr.,
         housing = Housing..tCO2e.yr.,
         food = Food..tCO2e.yr.,
         goods =  Goods..tCO2e.yr.,
         services = Services..tCO2e.yr., 
         total = Total..tCO2e.yr.)  %>%
  gather(transport, housing, food, goods, services, total, key = "Category",value = "emissions") %>%
  filter(Category != "total") %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_point(aes(y=leb, x=log(emissions), color=Category), alpha=I(0.05)) +
    geom_smooth(aes(y=leb, x=log(emissions), color=Category, group= Category), method = "glm") + 
  guides(alpha = FALSE) +
  theme_fivethirtyeight() + 
  scale_colour_wsj() + ggtitle("Log PerCap CO2equiv vs. Life Expectancy") + facet_wrap(~ Category)
